a.xlink:title: Consumer Notifications: A service that helps create, send, and manage various types of notifications to customers, including mobile text message notifications, push notifications, and email notifications.

Notification Queue: Temporarily holds and manages notification messages before they're delivered to their intended recipients. A digital “waiting room” where prioritized messages line up to be processed in the right order, at the right time.
Forward Proxy: A type of proxy server that sits between a client and the internet, facilitating requests from the client to external servers.
Invoke cloud service to send email
System Timer: Runs once per minute to inform Consumer Notifications it is time to check for tasks to perform.
Credit Application System: An in-house application used to process customer credit applications, assess creditworthiness, and manage credit risk.

Marketing CRM: A Customer Relationship Management (CRM) platform focused on digital marketing automation and analytics that helps businesses manage their relationships with customers and execute marketing campaigns across various channels.
Invoke cloud service to send email
Mail Relay: A Simple Mail Transfer Protocol (SMTP) relay transfers email from one SMTP server to another over the internet until reaching the intended recipent.
Consumer: The recipient of the email notification being sent.
Email Client: A software application that allows users to access, compose, and send email messages. It acts as the interface between the user and the mail server. Also known as a Mail User Agent.
